quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  30,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  30,2,"The Romans have been overcome"
  30,3,"in the nearest{1}land. But after having been overcome, they will overcome<i>(their enemy) </i>",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>a</i><i>dna</i> which can also mean ‘lowest’.]
  30,4,"in a few{1}years. The command belongs to Allah, in the past and in the future. And on that day, the believers will exult",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>bed’</i> which stands for numbers more than three and less than ten.]
  30,5,"in Allah’s support. He supports whomever He wills, and He is the Almighty, the Bestower of mercy."
